    <stitle>CAB: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - STRIKER PIN</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>STRIKER PIN</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600725">Figure 25</hotlnk>for Items in parentheses unless otherwise noted.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600725" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600725" filename="../figg16/G1600725.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Striker Pin</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOCK PILLAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DOOR STRIKER PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TORX HEAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SPACER SHIM</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Door striker pin (Item 2) mounted on lock pillar (Item 1) provides for positive engagement with the
                door latch assembly (Item 3,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600726">Figure 26</hotlnk>). Striker pin removal and installation requires a torx head
                tool (Item 3). Enlarged mounting hole in lock pillar permits adjustment.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600726" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600726" filename="../figg16/G1600726.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 26. Door Latch Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. REMOTE CONTROL HANDLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LATCH JAWS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DOOR LATCH ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a torx head tool (Item 3) to remove the door striker pin (Item 2) from the lock
                    pillar (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If spacer shims (Item 4) are used between the lock pillar (Item 1) and the door striker
                    pin (Item 2), save and reuse during installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If door striker pin (Item 2) was removed, position the spacer shims (Item 4), if so
                    equipped, in place on the lock pillar (Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door striker pin (Item 2) by threading it into the lock pillar (Item 1), with a
                    torx head tool (Item 3). Tighten to 34 to 50 ft-lbs. (46 to 68 N&#183;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If door striker pin adjustment is required, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_X1600712.xml" xrefid="x1600712">ADJUSTMENTS, STRIKER PIN AT LOCK
                        PILLAR</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
